13/04/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Hundreds of people fled their homes in northwestern BiH on Monday (12 April) after heavy weekend rains resulted in floods. 
Authorities evacuated residents in the towns of Jezero and Srbac; several roads were closed. 
A state of emergency has been declared in six municipalities, with more downpours expected. 
(OHR Sources, PBS BiH - 13/04/04; Reuters, Fena - 12/04/04)
